videos.description: Sooners WR Jeffery Mead makes an amazing catch on Oklahoma's opening drive for a 10-yard gain against Baylor.
videos.headline: Oklahoma completes awesome one-handed grab on opening drive

videos.description: Baker Mayfield puts Oklahoma on the board with a 15-yard rushing touchdown to put the Sooners up 7-0 over Baylor.
videos.headline: Mayfield's 15-yard run gives Oklahoma the early lead

videos.description: Oklahoma QB Baker Mayfield throws a great strike to Dede Westbrook, who shows off his athleticism to stay inbounds for a 29-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Sooners' Westbrook keeps his balance to get into the end zone

videos.description: Oklahoma's Jordan Evans intercepts Baylor's Seth Russell in the end zone and returns the ball nine yards.
videos.headline: Goal-line interception halts Baylor drive

videos.description: Samaje Perine run for 4-yards for a TD
videos.headline: S. Perine run for 4-yards for a TD

videos.description: KD Cannon breaks a tackle on his way to the end zone for a 24-yard touchdown for Baylor's first touchdown of the game against Oklahoma.
videos.headline: Baylor's Cannon stays on his feet for TD

videos.description: Baker Mayfield pass intercepted Orion Stewart return for a loss of 2 yards to the Okla 41
videos.headline: B. Mayfield pass intercepted by O. Stewart

videos.description: Oklahoma's Will Johnson forces Baylor's Seth Russell to fumble with less than a minute left in the half as the Sooners make the recovery.
videos.headline: Baylor fumbles with less than a minute to go in the half

videos.description: Oklahoma head coach Bob Stoops talks about the need to control the running game both offensively and defensively
videos.headline: Oklahoma head coach Bob Stoops talks about the need to control the running game both offensively and defensively

videos.description: Baker Mayfield goes deep to Dede Westbrook, who reaches back to make a nice touchdown catch in the third quarter. The play was reviewed and upheld.
videos.headline: Sooners' Westbrook extends to make great TD catch

videos.description: Jordan Evans intercepts Baylor QB Seth Russell and returns the ball 22 yards to the Baylor 1-yard line. The Sooners would score the 1-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Evans returns INT to the 1-yard line, sets up Sooners TD

videos.description: Samaje Perine run for 1-yard for a TD
videos.headline: S. Perine run for 1-yard for a TD

videos.description: Seth Russell goes down in the third quarter with an apparent leg injury.
videos.headline: Baylor QB Seth Russell suffers apparent leg injury

videos.description: Zach Smith run for 1-yard for a TD
videos.headline: Z. Smith run for 1-yard for a TD

videos.description: Oklahoma's Joe Mixon runs up the middle, breaks a tackle and pulls away from the defense for a 56-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Joe Mixon flashes the speed for 56-yard TD

videos.description: Zach Smith fires a strike to KD Cannon, who breaks a tackle and takes it all the way for a 62-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Baylor's Smith finds Cannon for 62-yard TD

videos.description: Oklahoma head coach Bob Stoops talks about his teams complete performance and his feelings on his 100th home win at Oklahoma
videos.headline: Oklahoma head coach Bob Stoops talks about his teams complete performance and his feelings on his 100th home win at Oklahoma

videos.description: Oklahoma v Baylor post game breakdown on Oklahoma's offensive performance led by QB Baker Mayfield in their 45-24 victory
videos.headline: Oklahoma v Baylor post game breakdown on Oklahoma's offensive performance led by QB Baker Mayfield in their 45-24 victory

videos.description: Baylor QB Seth Russell is carted off the field after suffering a dislocated ankle in the third quarter against Oklahoma.
videos.headline: Baylor QB Russell suffers dislocated left ankle

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One Play (Baylor QB Russell suffers dislocated left ankle NEW) 2016/11/12 ESHEET

videos.description: No. 11 Oklahoma is unbeaten in seven Big 12 games and has two ranked opponents remaining. But losses to Houston and Ohio State continue to dampen the Sooners' playoff hopes.
videos.headline: Oklahoma, atoning for early losses, still needs help
